ful optional prefixes are `World model:`, `Goal model:`, `Action model:`, `Recent findings:`, `Open questions:`, `Plan:`, and `Cross-level notes:`.\nWhen calling `python`, emit exactly the tool-call format shown elsewhere in this prompt for this model. Use only that format; do not add markdown fences, prose wrappers, or alternate tool-call syntax. Do not quote or place tool-call markup inside explanatory text; when you decide to call the tool, emit the tool call itself.\nIf you use MOUSE, include integer row and col arguments.\nEFFICIENCY BUDGET \u2014 your score on each level is (baseline_actions / your_actions)^2, so every wasted action costs you quadratically.\nLevel 2: you have used 59 actions; a strong score needs about 58 or fewer. You are 1.0x over the target.\nIf you are not steadily making progress toward the level goal, commit to your single best hypothesis and the shortest sequence that tests it \u2014 do not exhaustively scan rows/columns or enumerate every option. Test one idea, read the result, then decide.", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}, {"label": "THINKING", "content": "After UPx2, LEFTx4:\n- Left red: (16-19, 8-11) - shrunk from (16-19, 8-19)\n- Blue: (16-19, 12-31)\n- Right red: (24-27, 28-39) - reappeared!\nSo the left red shrunk when the blue moved to overlap with it, but it didn't disappear. And the right red reappeared.\nCurrent state:\n- Left red: (16-19, 8-11)\n- Blue: (16-19, 12-31)\n- Right red: (24-27, 28-39)\nI need to make the left red disappear. Previously, when I moved the blue to overlap with the right red, it disappeared. But when I moved the blue to overlap with the left red, it only shrunk.\nMaybe I need to fully cover the left red block. The left red is at (16-19, 8-11), which is 4x4. The blue is at (16-19, 12-31), which is 4x20. They overlap at cols 12-11... wait, that doesn't make sense. The blue is at cols 12-31 and the left red is at cols 8-11. They're adjacent but not overlapping.\nWait, let me re-read: left red (16-19,